==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pickeer
<hw>Pick*eer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Pickeered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Pickeering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>picorer</ets> to go marauding, orig., to go to steal cattle,
ultimately fr. L. <ets>pecus</ets>, <ets>pecoris</ets>, cattle; cf. F.
<ets>picor⟦eacute⟧e</ets>, Sp. <ets>pecorea</ets> robbery committed by
straggling soldiers.]</ety> <def>To make a raid for booty; to maraud;
also, to skirmish in advance of an army. See <er>Picaroon</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Burnet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

